From: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Date: Tue, 1 Oct 2013 19:04:40 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 22/35] net:drivers/net: Miscellaneous conversions to ETH_ALEN
Patch-mainline: v3.13-rc1
Git-commit: d458cdf712e0c671e8e819abb16ecd6e44f9daec (partial)
References: bsc#909363 FATE#317549

Convert the memset/memcpy uses of 6 to ETH_ALEN
where appropriate.

Also convert some struct definitions and u8 array
declarations of [6] to ETH_ALEN.

Signed-off-by: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Acked-by: Arend van Spriel <arend@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Gary Ching-Pang Lin <glin@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/netxen/netxen_nic_hw.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/netxen/netxen_nic_hw.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/netxen/netxen_nic_hw.c
@@ -648,7 +648,7 @@ nx_p3_sre_macaddr_change(struct netxen_a
 
 	mac_req = (nx_mac_req_t *)&req.words[0];
 	mac_req->op = op;
-	memcpy(mac_req->mac_addr, addr, 6);
+	memcpy(mac_req->mac_addr, addr, ETH_ALEN);
 
 	return netxen_send_cmd_descs(adapter, (struct cmd_desc_type0 *)&req, 1);
 }
